<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-515-951  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 515 951.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Oct 15 1990 v24 n42 p48(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Postscript challenger fades; Microsoft's page description languagenot expected until mid-1991. (Microsoft Corp. and Apple'sTrueimage and Truetype page description/font software; AdobeSystems Inc.'s PostScript)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Daly, James.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A report from the 1990 Seybold Professional Publishers Conferenceindicates that those interested in page description languagesshould expect a delay in the development of Microsoft Corp andApple's challenge to Adobe Systems Inc's PostScript.andP;  The TrueTypefont package and TrueImage printer software are not expected to beready until at least the middle of 1991.andP;  They should ship withOS/2, MS Windows and the new Macintosh System 7.0 operatingsystem.andP;  Thus it appears Adobe's anger over Apple's defection ispremature, but the uproar is spurring Adobe to update and enhanceits flagship product.andP;  Adobe executives and industry analystsexpect TrueType and TrueImage to have a hard time breaking intothe established base of PostScript users.andP;  Other events at theconference include C-Cube Microsystems Inc's introduction of imagecompression cards and Quark Inc's porting of Quark Xpress desktoppublishing software.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (product development)Apple Computer Inc. (product development).andO;Ticker:    MSFT; AAPL.andO;Product:   PostScript (Printer software) (competitions)TrueImage (Printer software) (product development)Truetype (Computer font) (product development).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentProduct DelayCompetitionPage Description LanguagesPrinter SoftwareSeybold Professional Publishers Conference.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>